        <dc:title>Shock Metamorphism Of Coconino Sandstone at Meteor Crater, Arizona</dc:title>
        <dc:date>August 10, 1971</dc:date>
        <bib:pages>5450-5073</bib:pages>
        <z:citationKey>kiefferShockMetamorphismCoconino1971</z:citationKey>
    </bib:Article>
    <bib:Memo rdf:about="#item_332">
        <rdf:value>&lt;div data-citation-items=&quot;%5B%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22itemData%22%3A%7B%22id%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%2C%22type%22%3A%22article-journal%22%2C%22citation-key%22%3A%22kiefferShockMetamorphismCoconino1971%22%2C%22container-title%22%3A%22Journal%20of%20Geophysical%20Research%22%2C%22issue%22%3A%2223%22%2C%22page%22%3A%225450-5073%22%2C%22title%22%3A%22Shock%20Metamorphism%20Of%20Coconino%20Sandstone%20at%20Meteor%20Crater%2C%20Arizona%22%2C%22volume%22%3A%2276%22%2C%22author%22%3A%5B%7B%22family%22%3A%22Kieffer%22%2C%22given%22%3A%22Susan%20Werner%22%7D%5D%2C%22issued%22%3A%7B%22date-parts%22%3A%5B%5B%221971%22%2C8%2C10%5D%5D%7D%7D%7D%5D&quot; data-schema-version=&quot;9&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;highlight&quot; data-annotation=&quot;%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FMFFKC85C%22%2C%22annotationKey%22%3A%229TZETD2I%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22%23ffd400%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%225462%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A13%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B42.12%2C258.297%2C231.702%2C266.622%5D%2C%5B40.92%2C247.572%2C234.612%2C255.564%5D%2C%5B41.04%2C236.652%2C126.016%2C244.644%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%225462%22%7D%7D&quot;&gt;“(1) remnant quartz grains, (2) symplekticregions, (3) opaque regions, (4) vesicular glass cores,and (5) calcite”&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;citation&quot; data-citation=&quot;%7B%22citationItems%22%3A%5B%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%225462%22%7D%5D%2C%22properties%22%3A%7B%7D%7D&quot;&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;citation-item&quot;&gt;Kieffer, 1971, p. 5462&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</rdf:value>
    </bib:Memo>
    <bib:Memo rdf:about="#item_46">
        <rdf:value>&lt;div data-citation-items=&quot;%5B%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22itemData%22%3A%7B%22id%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%2C%22type%22%3A%22article-journal%22%2C%22container-title%22%3A%22JOURNAL%20OF%20GEOPHYSICAL%20RESEARCH%22%2C%22issue%22%3A%2223%22%2C%22page%22%3A%225450-5073%22%2C%22title%22%3A%22Shock%20Metamorphism%20Of%20Coconino%20Sandstone%22%2C%22volume%22%3A%2276%22%2C%22author%22%3A%5B%7B%22family%22%3A%22KIEFFER%22%2C%22given%22%3A%22SUSAN%20WERNER%22%7D%5D%2C%22issued%22%3A%7B%22date-parts%22%3A%5B%5B%221971%22%2C8%2C10%5D%5D%7D%7D%7D%5D&quot; data-schema-version=&quot;9&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Classes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;highlight&quot; data-annotation=&quot;%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FMFFKC85C%22%2C%22annotationKey%22%3A%229869UYJY%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22%23f799d1%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%225456%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A7%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B49.08%2C355.944%2C108.541%2C366.432%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%225456%22%7D%7D&quot;&gt;“Class 1a rock”&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;citation&quot; data-citation=&quot;%7B%22citationItems%22%3A%5B%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%225456%22%7D%5D%2C%22properties%22%3A%7B%7D%7D&quot;&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;citation-item&quot;&gt;KIEFFER, 1971, p. 5456&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Weakly shocked, no high pressure phases, 95% more quartz, and a) remnant porosity and b) no remnant porosity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(a) do not differ in macroscopic appearance from unshocked CSS, less porosity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(b) fragile, fine-grained, and friable (dry), fracturing (concussion)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;highlight&quot; data-annotation=&quot;%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FMFFKC85C%22%2C%22annotationKey%22%3A%2224RLHCJX%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22%238fdef9%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%225457%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A8%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B252.24%2C448.644%2C310.64%2C457.062%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%225457%22%7D%7D&quot;&gt;“Class 2 rocks.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;moderately shocked, 80-95% quartz, 2-5% coesite, 3-10% glass, no porosity, interlocked, grain size reduced (slightly), change in shape w/o fracturing and strain suggests plastic deformation compression, isotropic regions,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;highlight&quot; data-annotation=&quot;%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FMFFKC85C%22%2C%22annotationKey%22%3A%22GN8NUVKI%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22%237df066%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%225459%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A10%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B253.56%2C616.02%2C318.576%2C626.37%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%225459%22%7D%7D&quot;&gt;“Class 3 rocks.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;moderately shocked 45-80% quartz, 18-32% coesite, 0-20% glass, boundaries between grains unclear, plastic deformation removes void spaces, symplektic region surrounding quartz&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;highlight&quot; data-annotation=&quot;%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FMFFKC85C%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%225462%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A13%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B50.04%2C402.01152%2C103.84703999999999%2C410.00352000000004%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%225462%22%7D%7D&quot;&gt;“Class 4 rocks”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;strongly shocked, 15-45% quartz, 10-30% coesite, 20-75% glass, elongated, aligned fractures/vesicles, calcite in fractures/vesicles, &lt;span class=&quot;highlight&quot; data-annotation=&quot;%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FMFFKC85C%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%225462%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A13%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B48.12%2C478.00056%2C80.29056%2C485.32656%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%225462%22%7D%7D&quot;&gt;“Fig. 11a”&lt;/span&gt;, bordered symplektic/opaque, vesicles indicate gas was present as pressure was released- probs water,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;highlight&quot; data-annotation=&quot;%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FMFFKC85C%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%225463%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A14%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B48%2C161.64732%2C104.83487999999998%2C170.19432%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%225463%22%7D%7D&quot;&gt;“Class 5 rock”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;very strongly shocked, 0-15% quartz, 0-5% coesite, 80-100% glass, flowed stretched glass, vesicles, remnant grains of quartz,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;no detectable to trace amounts of stishovite in all classes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation&quot; data-citation=&quot;%7B%22citationItems%22%3A%5B%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%225455%22%7D%5D%2C%22properties%22%3A%7B%7D%7D&quot;&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;citation-item&quot;&gt;KIEFFER, 1971, p. 5455&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</rdf:value>
    </bib:Memo>
    <bib:Memo rdf:about="#item_47">
        <rdf:value>&lt;div data-citation-items=&quot;%5B%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22itemData%22%3A%7B%22id%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%2C%22type%22%3A%22article-journal%22%2C%22container-title%22%3A%22JOURNAL%20OF%20GEOPHYSICAL%20RESEARCH%22%2C%22issue%22%3A%2223%22%2C%22page%22%3A%225450-5073%22%2C%22title%22%3A%22SHOCK%20METAMORPHIS1Vf%20OF%20COCONINO%20SANDSTONE%22%2C%22volume%22%3A%2276%22%2C%22author%22%3A%5B%7B%22family%22%3A%22KIEFFER%22%2C%22given%22%3A%22SUSAN%20WERNER%22%7D%5D%2C%22issued%22%3A%7B%22date-parts%22%3A%5B%5B%221971%22%2C8%2C10%5D%5D%7D%7D%7D%5D&quot; data-schema-version=&quot;9&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;highlight&quot; data-annotation=&quot;%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FMFFKC85C%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%225466%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A17%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B311.52%2C164.48184%2C437.37431999999995%2C172.69584%5D%2C%5B243.24%2C153.75636%2C275.9142%2C161.63736%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%225466%22%7D%7D&quot;&gt;“energy deposition in a porous material”&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</rdf:value>
    </bib:Memo>
    <bib:Memo rdf:about="#item_48">
        <rdf:value>&lt;div data-citation-items=&quot;%5B%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22itemData%22%3A%7B%22id%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%2C%22type%22%3A%22article-journal%22%2C%22container-title%22%3A%22JOURNAL%20OF%20GEOPHYSICAL%20RESEARCH%22%2C%22issue%22%3A%2223%22%2C%22page%22%3A%225450-5073%22%2C%22title%22%3A%22Shock%20Metamorphism%20Of%20Coconino%20Sandstone%22%2C%22volume%22%3A%2276%22%2C%22author%22%3A%5B%7B%22family%22%3A%22KIEFFER%22%2C%22given%22%3A%22SUSAN%20WERNER%22%7D%5D%2C%22issued%22%3A%7B%22date-parts%22%3A%5B%5B%221971%22%2C8%2C10%5D%5D%7D%7D%7D%5D&quot; data-schema-version=&quot;9&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;how vesicles in glassy?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;highlight&quot; data-annotation=&quot;%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FMFFKC85C%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%225463%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A14%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B193.79999999999998%2C538.04184%2C231.30023999999995%2C546.25584%5D%2C%5B38.88%2C527.41152%2C228.83712%2C535.4035200000001%5D%2C%5B38.52%2C515.91216%2C229.79999999999995%2C524.34816%5D%2C%5B38.64%2C505.30668000000003%2C231.83460000000005%2C513.40968%5D%2C%5B38.76%2C494.00183999999996%2C229.86864%2C502.21583999999996%5D%2C%5B38.52%2C483.01152%2C231.6096%2C491.00352000000004%5D%2C%5B38.64%2C471.92184%2C233.30615999999995%2C480.13584%5D%2C%5B38.64%2C461.17152%2C228.12096000000003%2C469.16352%5D%2C%5B38.52%2C449.98668000000004%2C229.6182%2C458.08968%5D%2C%5B38.4%2C438.97152%2C229.9248%2C446.96352%5D%2C%5B38.4%2C429.81444%2C227.48352000000003%2C436.36343999999997%5D%2C%5B38.28%2C416.577%2C228.816%2C424.902%5D%2C%5B38.4%2C405.70668%2C228.90000000000003%2C413.80967999999996%5D%2C%5B38.52%2C394.497%2C230.37900000000002%2C402.822%5D%2C%5B38.4%2C383.60184%2C228.33431999999996%2C391.81584%5D%2C%5B38.4%2C372.70668%2C229.84404%2C380.80967999999996%5D%2C%5B38.16%2C361.64184%2C52.962959999999995%2C369.85584%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%225463%22%7D%7D&quot;&gt;“Kennedy et al. demonstrated that a critical end point for the univariant equilibrium melting curve of the Si02-H.•O system exists at 9.7 kb and 1080øC. Thus, at pressures greater than 10 kb and temperatures greater than 1100øC, complete intermixing of the SiO• and H•O phases occurs. If water were incorporated into the SiO2 at pressures above 10 kb, some, water would exsolve and form vesicles on release to zero pressure. These observations on the existence of vesicles and on the proximity of fused SiO• to quartz suggest that water in the pores of the rock initially may have played an important role in allowing parts of the rock to melt at relatively low temperatures because they were wet”&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;citation&quot; data-citation=&quot;%7B%22citationItems%22%3A%5B%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%225463%22%7D%5D%2C%22properties%22%3A%7B%7D%7D&quot;&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;citation-item&quot;&gt;KIEFFER, 1971, p. 5463&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SO: water exsolves forming vesicles as water was incorporated into SiO2. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</rdf:value>
    </bib:Memo>
    <bib:Memo rdf:about="#item_45">
        <rdf:value>&lt;div data-citation-items=&quot;%5B%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%5D%2C%22itemData%22%3A%7B%22id%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FOLWMPY2p%2Fitems%2FACVYL98D%22%2C%22type%22%3A%22article-journal%22%2C%22container-title%22%3A%22JOURNAL%20OF%20GEOPHYSICAL%20RESEARCH%22%2C%22issue%22%3A%2223%22%2C%22page%22%3A%225450-5073%22%2C%22title%22%3A%22SHOCK%20METAMORPHIS1Vf%20OF%20COCONINO%20SANDSTONE%22%2C%22volume%22%3A%2276%22%2C%22author%22%3A%5B%7B%22family%22%3A%22KIEFFER%22%2C%22given%22%3A%22SUSAN%20WERNER%22%7D%5D%2C%22issued%22%3A%7B%22date-parts%22%3A%5B%5B%221971%22%2C8%2C10%5D%5D%7D%7D%7D%5D&quot; data-schema-version=&quot;9&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Meteor Crater in Canyon Diablo region, S of Colorado Plateau&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coconino SS, Toroweap, Kaibab LM, and Moenkopi FM&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;overturned flap (with inverted stratigraphy (5451-5452&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</rdf:value>
